INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (15, 1, '2014-01-30 19:12:39', '2014-01-30 19:12:39', '<p><b>What is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is The Australian Graphic Supply Co, a design studio originally from Australia, now based in Oviedo Spain. We are passionate about creating gorgeous hand lettering, beautiful brands, and lovely websites.  For a bit more info, see our <a title="About" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//about">About page</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b><em>Who</em> is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is run by husband and wife team Dave and Laura Coleman. More reading at this <a title="The \'Us\' in The Australian Graphic Supply Co." href="http://dev.theagsc.com//community/the-us-in-the-australian-graphic-supply-co">blog post</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b>What does The AGSC do?<br /></b>Check out what <a title="Services" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//services">services</a> we offer here.</p>\r\n<p><b>Where are you based?<br /></b>We are based in Oviedo, Asturias, a small city in the Northwest of Spain.  We are currently living here on a teaching scholarship (Laura teaches English in a high school here 12 hours a week).  We absolutely love it, and feel so blessed that in half an hour we can be sitting by the beach, or in 45 minutes be in the snowy mountains.  If you want to know more about Oviedo and our life here, check out <a title="Spain Blog" href="http://daveandlaura.in/spain" target="_blank">our travel blog</a>.  </p>\r\n<p><b>I don’t live in Spain, can you still work on my project?<br /></b>Most definitely!  Thanks to the power of the internet your proximity to us doesn’t affect our ability to work with you.  We have so much fun working with clients from all around the world, and use Skype/email to chat, and nifty services like <a title="Red Pen" href="http://redpen.io" target="_blank">redpen.io</a> for feedback and comments. In saying all that, we know that some projects benefit greatly from face-to-face chats (and coffees). Let us know if that\'s you, and we can discuss travel arrangements to anywhere around the globe.</p>\r\n<p><b>How much do you charge?</b><br /> Design jobs are case by case, in that every detail varies, every need is slightly different, and every end product is unique.  Because of this, we don’t work with fixed prices, but get to know you, and what you are after.  Once we\'ve chatted a little bit, and understood your project we can give you a quote.  <a title="Email The AGSC" href="mailto:hello@theagsc.com">Send us an email</a> or head over to our <a title="Contact" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//contact">contact page</a> to get in touch with us!</p>\r\n<p><b>Do you accept rush jobs?<br /></b>We do. We understand that some projects have a tight deadline, and we would love to help you out with that.  An additional fee covers overtime hours as we crank into overdrive.  <a title="Email The AGSC" href="mailto:hello@theagsc.com">Shoot us an email</a> with the details of the project, and the deadline, and we\'ll see what we can do.</p>\r\n<p><b>What’s the best way to reach you?<br /></b>The best way to reach us is through our email (<a title="Email The AGSC" href="mailto: hello@theagsc.com">hello@theagsc.com</a>), or through our contact form.  Our office hours are 8:30am - 5:00pm (CET), so if we receive emails outside of this time we will get back to you as soon as possible, within business hours. </p>\r\n<p><b>Do you code websites?</b><br /> Heck yes we do. Coding is one of the few logic-based things that Dave is good at haha. We love love developing websites that look good and feel even better to interact with. We also have a super skilled developer that is our go-to guy for the intense stuff. Basically, we\'ve got you covered.</p>\r\n<p><b>How long do projects normally take?<br /></b>Our hand lettering jobs (logos, lettering commissions etc…) normally take between 3 - 6 weeks to complete, with websites taking between 2 - 3 months.  However, this is just rough ball park, as every project will differ depending on the scope of the job.  </p>\r\n<p><b>Can I navigate through The AGSC using keyboard shortcuts?<br /></b>Sure thing! Were hoping you\'d ask. See the <a title="Keyboard Shortcuts" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//keyboard-shortcuts">Cheat Sheet page</a>.</p>', 'FAQ\'s', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'faqs', '', '', '2014-03-07 15:18:04', '2014-03-07 15:18:04', '', 13, 'http://newsite.theagsc.com/?page_id=15', 14, 'page', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (690, 1, '2014-03-07 15:18:04', '2014-03-07 15:18:04', '<p><b>What is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is The Australian Graphic Supply Co, a design studio originally from Australia, now based in Oviedo Spain. We are passionate about creating gorgeous hand lettering, beautiful brands, and lovely websites.  For a bit more info, see our <a title="About" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//about">About page</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b><em>Who</em> is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is run by husband and wife team Dave and Laura Coleman. More reading at this <a title="The \'Us\' in The Australian Graphic Supply Co." href="http://dev.theagsc.com//community/the-us-in-the-australian-graphic-supply-co">blog post</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b>What does The AGSC do?<br /></b>Check out what <a title="Services" href="http://dev.theagsc.com//services">services</a> we offer here.</p>\r\n<p><b>Where are you based?<br /></b>We are based in Oviedo, Asturias, a small city in the Northwest of Spain.  We are currently living here on a teaching scholarship (Laura teaches English in a high school here 12 hours a week).  We absolutely love it, and feel so blessed that in half an hour we can be sitting by the beach, or in 45 minutes be in the snowy mountains.  If you want to know more about Oviedo and our life here, check out <a title="Spain Blog" href="http://daveandlaura.in/spain" target="_blank">our travel blog</a>.  </p>\r\n<p><b>I don’t live in Spain, can you still work on my project?<br /></b>Most definitely!  Thanks to the power of the internet your proximity to us doesn’t affect our ability to work with you.  We have so much fun working with clients from all around the world, and use Skype/email to chat, and nifty services like <a title="Red Pen" href="http://redpen.io" target="_blank">redpen.io</a> for feedback and comments. In saying all that, we know that some projects benefit greatly from face-to-face chats (and coffees). Let us know if that\'s you, and we can discuss travel arrangeme