INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (845, 2, '2014-04-23 21:56:12', '2014-04-23 21:56:12', '<p>Even before I met Dave, and consequently fell into the design world, I loved stamps.  There is something about holding a tactile object, choosing your ink, choosing your paper, and creating something out of the two.  When I was about 11 I got into this phase where I would make little cards using the stamps as a base to create a watercolour piece, or emboss the stamp image – I thought it was just about the most creative and cool thing an 11 year old could possibly do.</p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/02.jpg" alt="Fig. 01"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 01</figcaption></p>\r\n<p>As we went about branding The AGSC, we both could not wait to get our hands on a custom stamp.  We started researching, and came across <a href="http://www.simonstamp.com/">Simon’s Stamps</a>, an American custom rubber stamp manufacturer.  After getting in contact with them, we put through our order, and less than 24 hours later, it was shipped to Spain.  Nice and easy – definitely check them out.</p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/03.jpg" alt="Fig. 02"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 02</figcaption></p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/04.jpg" alt="Fig. 03"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 03</figcaption></p>\r\n<p>In other news, despite our luck with Simon’s Stamps, we haven’t had much luck with the Spanish postal service!  Our dear <a href="https://dribbble.com/shots/1455093-Matilda?list=users&amp;offset=8">Matilda prints</a> were detained upon entry into Spain, and we were told we would have to pay a couple hundred euros to get them released, so they are currently taking a tour around the world as they are sent back to the States; to then be sent to Australia.  Spain always keeps us on our toes.  We are hoping to have them back up in the <a href="http://dev.theagsc.com//shop">The AGSC Shop</a> within the next month!</p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/05.jpg" alt="Fig. 04"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 04</figcaption></p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/06.jpg" alt="Fig. 05"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 05</figcaption></p>\r\n<p>Our fingers are itching to stamp some stuff, so if you\'d like, send us your postal address (<a href="mailto:feedback@theagsc.com">feedback@theagsc.com</a>) and we\'ll craft you a little bit of hand lettering on some nice paper, sealed with a <s>kiss</s> stamp. Go on!</p>\r\n<p><img src="http://dev.theagsc.com//wp-content/themes/theagsclive/images/blog/news/stamp/07.jpg" alt="Fig. 06"/></p>\r\n<p><figcaption>Fig. 06</figcaption></p>\r\n<p>Be sure to <a href="http://eepurl.com/MEK_z">subscribe</a> to stay in touch with myself and Dave as we share more tutorials, articles, our own projects, dreams, interviews (we have some really interesting folks lined up to chat with here on the blog), inspiration and a bunch more.</p>\r\n<p>L</p>\r\n', 'We Got a Stamp (The Modern Designer\'s Rite of Passage)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'we-got-a-stamp-the-modern-designers-rite-of-passage', '', '', '2014-04-23 22:04:51', '2014-04-23 22:04:51', '', 0, 'http://theagsc.com/?p=845', 0, 'post', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (847, 2, '2014-04-17 14:43:14', '2014-04-17 14:43:14', '<p>Even before I met Dave, and consequently fell into the design world, I loved stamps.  There is something about holding a tactile object, choosing your ink, choosing your paper, and creating something out of the two.  When I was about 11, I got into this phase where I would make cards using the stamps as a base to create a watercolour piece, or emboss the stamp image (which I thought was the most creative and cool thing an 11 year old could do).<br /> <br /> As we went about branding The AGSC, we both could not wait to get our hands on a custom stamp of The AGSC logo.  We started researching, and came across <a title="Simon\'s Stamps" href="http://www.simonstamp.com/" target="_blank">Simon’s Stamps</a>, an American custom rubber stamp manufacturer.  After getting in contact with them, we put through our order, and less than 24 hours later, it was shipped to Spain.  <br /> <br /> Despite our luck with Simon’s Stamps, we haven’t had much luck with the Spanish post.  Our dear <a title="Matilda Print" href="http://dribbble.com/shots/1455093-Matilda?list=users&amp;offset=6" target="_blank">Matilda</a> prints (link to Dribbble post) were detained upon entry into Spain, and we were told we would have to pay a couple hundred euros to get them released, so they are currently taking a tour around the world, as they are sent back to the U.S. to then be sent to Australia.  Spain always keeps us on our toes.  We are hoping to have them back up in the store within the next month!<br /> <br /> We would love to get our stamp worked in, so if any of you want, send your postal address to us at <a href="mailto:feedback@theagsc.com" target="_blank">feedback@theagsc.com</a>, and we’ll send you a handwritten note, complete with our new stamped logo for you to check out.</p>', 'The AGSC Stamp', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '845-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 14:43:14', '2014-04-17 14:43:14', '', 845, 'http://theagsc.com/community/845-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (846, 2, '2014-04-17 14:35:57', '2014-04-17 14:35:57', '<p>Even before I met Dave, and consequently fell into the design world, I loved stamps.  There is something about holding a tactile object, choosing your ink, choosing your paper, and creating something out of the two.  When I was about 11, I got into this phase where I would make cards using the stamps as a base to create a watercolour piece, or emboss the stamp image (which I thought was the most creative and cool thing an 11 year old could do).<br /> <br /> As we went about branding The AGSC, we both could not wait to get our hands on a custom stamp of The AGSC logo.  We started researching, and came across <a title="Simon\'s Stamps" href="http://www.simonstamp.com/" target="_blank">Simon’s Stamps</a>, an American custom rubber stamp manufacturer.  After getting in contact with them, we put through our order, and less than 24 hours later, it was shipped to Spain.  <br /> <br /> The great thing about Simon’s Stamps is that they are so affordable, and quick to ship.  Within about two weeks we had found Simon’s Stamps, chatted to them, had our stamp produced, sent to Spain, and delivered safely to our letterbox.  <br /> <br /> Despite our luck with Simon’s Stamps, we haven’t had much luck with the Spanish post.  Our dear <a title="Matilda Print" href="http://dribbble.com/shots/1455093-Matilda?list=users&amp;offset=6" target="_blank">Matilda</a> prints (link to Dribbble post) were detained upon entry into Spain, and we were told we would have to pay a couple hundred euros to get them released, so they are currently taking a tour around the world, as they are sent back to the U.S. to then be sent to Australia.  Spain always leaves us on our toes.  We are hoping to have them back up in the store within the next month!<br /> <br /> We would love to get our stamp worked in, so if any of you want, send your postal address to us at <a href="mailto:feedback@theagsc.com" target="_blank">feedback@theagsc.com</a>, and we’ll send you a handwritten note, complete with our new stamped logo for you to check out.</p>', 'The AGSC Stamp', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '845-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 14:35:57', '2014-04-17 14:35:57', '', 845, 'http://theagsc.com/community/845-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
