INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (287, 2, '2014-03-03 11:40:07', '2014-03-03 11:40:07', '<p><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">Welcome to The Australian Graphic Supply Co.  We are so proud to release our business, and to announce that The AGSC is a partnership, owned and operated by us, Dave and Laura. </span></p>\r\n<p>We got married on the 3rd of December 2012. That day we forged an unbreakable team in marriage. On the 28th of February 2013 I left my full time job as a junior in a design agency in Sydney to start full time freelancing.  At the same time, Laura left her retail job, and together Laura and I created the AGSC - starting another unbreakable bond... in business. </p>\r\n<p>It turned out to be our best business decision to date; the harmony with which we work as family is the same harmony we bring to working together (thankfully). Here\'s a few words on why we work.<em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>Laura – Managing Director</em><i><br /> </i>Laura has a wonderful brain for systems, organisation &amp; finances. If you email us you are likely to end up chatting to Laura (and be better off for it). She has a keen sense for good design - and <em>tells me</em> when I\'m not producing it. She\'s not one to tiptoe through any tulips; she was blessed with a frankness I can only dream of wielding. She is a fantastic photographer, and my favourite second shooter. Laura can juggle a remarkable number of processes at once, so is invaluable in keeping website development on track, updating our daily tasks, following up on projects and generally ensuring everything is running smoothly for our clients.</p>\r\n<p>She\'s also an extremely handsome woman, but that doesn\'t tend to have as direct an impact on business. Still worth mentioning though.<em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>Dave – Creative Director</em><br /> Dave is the most creative person I know.  My earliest memories of Dave from when we had first met were of him drawing cartoons on customers’ invoices; he was always seemingly creating, no matter the time or place.  Dave’s passion for the design world is the driving force behind The AGSC.  He is an incredibly hard working designer, who strives for the best.  He doesn’t take no as an answer, and is always thinking outside of the box, trying to create bigger and better.  Dave has a great eye, whether that be for lettering, website design, photography, music; he is simply incredibly gifted.  Dave exudes lettering – it has become a huge of our lives, and an integral part of our business. </p>\r\n<p>I love that Dave exudes such an energetic, exuberant personality; continually finding reasons to laugh, and make this already incredible job more rewarding.</p>\r\n<p>We are incredibly proud and excited to be finally releasing The AGSC, and making our partnership in business known to the world.  We cannot wait to share more with you about ourselves, about our business, and about design. </p>\r\n<p>Dave and Laura</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'The \'us\' in The Australian Graphic Supply Co', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '286-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-03 11:40:07', '2014-03-03 11:40:07', '', 286, 'http://newsite.theagsc.com/community/286-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (905, 1, '2014-04-23 20:54:02', '2014-04-23 20:54:02', '<p>Even before I met Dave, and consequently fell into the design world, I loved stamps.  There is something about holding a tactile object, choosing your ink, choosing your paper, and creating something out of the two.  When I was about 11 I got into this phase where I would make little cards using the stamps as a base to create a watercolour piece, or emboss the stamp image – I thought it was just about the most creative and cool thing an 11 year old could possibly do.</p>\r\n<p>As we went about branding The AGSC, we both could not wait to get our hands on a custom stamp.  We started researching, and came across <a href="http://www.simonstamp.com/">Simon’s Stamps</a>, an American custom rubber stamp manufacturer.  After getting in contact with them, we put through our order, and less than 24 hours later, it was shipped to Spain.  Nice and easy – definitely check them out.</p>\r\n<p>In other news, despite our luck with Simon’s Stamps, we haven’t had much luck with the Spanish postal service!  Our dear <a href="https://dribbble.com/shots/1455093-Matilda?list=users&amp;offset=8">Matilda prints</a> were detained upon entry into Spain, and we were told we would have to pay a couple hundred euros to get them released, so they are currently taking a tour around the world as they are sent back to the States;to then be sent to Australia.  Spain always keeps us on our toes.  We are hoping to have them back up in the <a href="http://dev.theagsc.com//shop">The AGSC Shop</a> within the next month!</p>\r\n<p>Our fingers are itching to stamp some stuff, so if you\'d like, send us your postal address (<a href="mailto:feedback@theagsc.com">feedback@theagsc.com</a>) and we\'ll craft you a little bit of hand lettering on some nice paper, sealed with a <s>kiss</s> stamp. Go on!</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to <a href="http://eepurl.com/MEK_z">subscribe</a> to stay in touch with myself and Dave as we share more tutorials, articles, our own projects, dreams, interviews (we have some really interesting folks lined up to chat with here on the blog), inspiration and a bunch more.</p>\r\n<p>L</p>\r\n', 'We Got a Stamp (The Modern Designer\'s Rite of Passage)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '845-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-23 20:54:02', '2014-04-23 20:54:02', '', 845, 'http://theagsc.com/community/845-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
