INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (525, 1, '2014-03-05 12:01:42', '2014-03-05 12:01:42', '<p><b>What is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is The Australian Graphic Supply Co, a design studio originally from Australia, now based in Oviedo Spain.  It was founded early 2013. We are passionate about creating gorgeous hand lettering, beautiful brands, and lovely websites.  For a bit more info, see our About page.</p>\r\n<p><b><em>Who</em> is The AGSC?<br /></b>The AGSC is run by husband and wife team Dave and Laura Coleman. More reading at this blog post.</p>\r\n<p><b>What does The AGSC do?<br /></b>Check out what services we offer here.</p>\r\n<p><b>Where are you based?<br /></b>We are based in Oviedo, Asturias, a small city in the Northwest of Spain.  We are currently living here on a teaching scholarship (Laura teaches English in a high school here 12 hours a week).  We absolutely, and feel so blessed that in half an hour we can be sitting by the beach, or in 45 minutes be in the snowy mountains.  If you want to know more about Oviedo and our life here, check out <a title="Spain Blog" href="http://daveandlaura.in/spain" target="_blank">our travel blog</a>.  </p>\r\n<p><b>I don’t live in Spain, can you still work on my project?<br /></b>Most definitely!  Thanks to the power of the internet your proximity to us doesn’t affect our ability to work with you.  We have so much fun working with clients from all around the world, and use Skype/email to chat, and nifty services like <a title="Red Pen" href="http://redpen.io" target="_blank">redpen.io</a> for feedback and comments. In saying all that, we know that some projects benefit greatly from face-to-face chats (and coffees). Let us know if that\'s you, and we can discuss travel arrangements to anywhere on the globe.</p>\r\n<p><b>How much do you charge?<br /></b>Design jobs are case by case, in that every detail varies, every need is slightly different, and every end product is unique.  Because of this, we don’t work with fixed prices, but get to know you, and what you are after.  Once we’ve chatted a little bit, and understood your project we can give you a quote.  Send us an email (LINK) or head over to our contact form to get in touch with us!</p>\r\n<p><b>Do you accept rush jobs?<br /></b>We understand that some projects have a tight deadline, and we would love to help you out with that!  For an additional fee, we accept rush jobs; shoot us an email with the details of the project, and the deadline, and we’ll see what we can do!</p>\r\n<p><b>What’s the best way to reach you?<br /></b>The best way to reach us is through our email (hello@theagsc.com), or through our contact form.  Our office hours are 8:30am - 5:00pm (CET), so if we receive emails outside of this time we will get back to you as soon as possible, within business hours. </p>\r\n<p><b>Do you code websites?<br /></b>One of the biggest joys in designing websites, is that step where you take a design, and make it live.  There is such beauty in turning something static into a functional site, and we pride ourselves on our coding ability.  We also sometimes contract out to an amazing developer for those trickier processes (web apps etc…), and he is one of the best in the business.</p>\r\n<p><b>What is your lettering process?<br /></b>Take a look at our lettering process blog here.</p>\r\n<p><b>How long do projects normally take?<br /></b>Our hand lettering jobs (logos, lettering commissions etc…) normally take between 3 - 6 weeks to complete, with websites taking between 2 - 3 months.  However, this is just rough ball park, as every project will differ depending on the scope of the job.  </p>\r\n<p><b>Can I navigate through The AGSC using keyboard shortcuts?<br /></b>Sure thing! </p>', 'FAQ\'s', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-05 12:01:42', '2014-03-05 12:01:42', '', 15, 'http://newsite.theagsc.com/community/15-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
