span> and re-vectorised, however, it weighed in at a ungainly 2806 points and 222Kb. To be fair, this difference is all but completely unnoticeable, but if you do feel led to go through and give some love to your final file, the hard working folks over at <a href="http://www.astutegraphics.com/" title="ai">Astute Graphics</a> have got some very powerful plugins for <span class="ai">Ai</span>, such as <a href="http://www.astutegraphics.com/software/vectorscribe/">VectorScribe</a>, which offers (among a myriad of other fantastic tools) a <code>Smart Remove Brush Tool</code>, that automatically finds and removes unnecessary points along your vector paths.</p>\r\n<p><div id="ref"></p>\r\n<h3>References</h3><p></div></p>\r\n<p><div id="ref-01" class="ref"><sup> <code>[1]</code> </sup>Let\'s not forget there are a bunch of alternatives out there; <a href="http://www.inkscape.org/en/">Inkscape</a>, <a href="http://bohemiancoding.com/sketch/">Sketch</a>, <a href="http://www.gimp.org/">GIMP</a> etc. Let us know if and what you prefer about these editors over Adobe products.</div></p>\r\n', 'Quick Tip #01: Returning Your Artwork to Vector After Editing in Photoshop', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '918-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-30 12:30:49', '2014-04-30 12:30:49', '', 918, 'http://theagsc.com/community/918-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
